label: AB12C3_cI32_229_a_h_b-001
title: Model of Austenite Structure (cI32)
comments: Austenitic steels are alloys of iron and other metals with an averaged face-centered cubic structure. This model represents one approximation for an austenite steel. If we set $y_{3} = 1/4$, the atoms are on the sites of an fcc lattice.
